	<exercise xml:id="bac-approx-solutions" component="not-workbook">
		<introduction>
			<p>
				After his first beer, Stephen's blood alcohol content (BAC) was already 0.04 and as he continued to drink, his BAC level rose 45% per hour. The equation is <me>S = 0.04 \ast 1.45^H</me> where <m>S</m> is Stephen's BAC and <m>H</m> is the time, measured in hours.
			</p>
			<p>
				<em>
					(Story also appears in 
